# InvokeAI Integration

PhotoMapAI works particularly well as a browser for the gallery produced by [InvokeAI](https://invoke-ai.github.io/InvokeAI/), the open-source generative-image application. When PhotoMapAI is connected to a running InvokeAI backend, you also gain three actions inside the metadata drawer that send images back into InvokeAI for further work.

## Introduction

InvokeAI is a free, locally-hosted text-to-image generator built around Stable Diffusion and related models. You can download it from the [InvokeAI project page](https://github.com/invoke-ai/InvokeAI). PhotoMapAI does not require InvokeAI to be installed — every feature described elsewhere in the User Guide works on any folder of images — but if you do generate images with InvokeAI, the integration described here lets you index, search, and remix that gallery from the same interface.

